Class LinkedListRecursive.ListNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.util.LinkedListRecursive.ListNode
  • Enclosing class:
    LinkedListRecursive<E>

    private class LinkedListRecursive.ListNode
extends java.lang.Object
    Inner class defines state of ListNodes that make up LinkedListRecursive's elements. Behavior is provided for recursive functionality of outer methods.
    Author:
    Nick Garner

        public E remove(int index)

        Returns:

      • remove

        public boolean remove(E element)
        Recursive behavior of outer remove(E) method. Traverses the list until reaching a node with the given element, then removes that node, decrements the list size, and returns true. Returns false if element is not found.
        Parameters:
        element - Data of the node to remove.
        Returns:
        True if node removed successfully, false otherwise.

      • set

        element - Data to replace the given node's data with.
        Returns:
        Old data contained in the node.

        public boolean contains(E element)
